6000|$|The Countryman. [...] "You {{know how}} much, {{for some time}} past, the editions of the <b>Elzevirs</b> have been in demand. The fancy for them has even {{penetrated}} into the country. I am acquainted with a man there who denies himself necessaries, {{for the sake of}} collecting into a library (where other books are scarce enough) as many little <b>Elzevirs</b> as he can lay his hands upon. He is dying of hunger, and his consolation {{is to be able to}} say, 'I have all the poets whom the <b>Elzevirs</b> printed. I have ten examples of each of them, all with red letters, and all of the right date.' This, no doubt, is a craze, for, good as the books are, if he kept them to read them, one example of each would be enough." ...|$|R
